        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 10:00AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 958 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Hobart, moving northeast at 75 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and an abundant amount of pea size
hail that could cover the ground.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rocky, Sentinel, Cordell, Corn, Bessie, Clinton, Cloud Chief,
Altus-Lugert Lake, Lone Wolf, Hobart, and Dill City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
